Liberia's first President while his entourage were in the USA, a big fire ruined the documents the Liberians brought to the USA for adoption of a constitution and other charters. And for a better understanding of this time period, the National Government had to conduct election with all necessary procedures, so the National Government and Congress of Liberia chose the constitution in existence today preserved since 6 May 1847. 

The most significant religious work to Liberia is from the Americans in 1844, when the Vice President, Rev William MacArthur, was the only Methodist Episcopal preacher in Liberia. This Methodist church service and the talk about self administration in Religion gave the Liberians an Ideology which even in in 2007, and still predominant for many Liberians. 1 out of every 5 persons in the world is a Christian. Many are Presbyterians, Methodist, Catholic, Episcopalian, Anglican and every other Protestant denomination.
